    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Call implementing function according to args values Print error message into System.err stream, if:
      • args don't match any supported modes;
      • args cannot be casted to required types.
      • ImplerException was thrown by according implementing function;
      Parameters:
      args - describes working mode, currently support:
      • [class token, root path] for implement(Class, Path)
      • ["-jar", class token, jar file path] for implementJar(Class, Path)

    • printErrorMessage

      private static void printErrorMessage()
      Notify of main(String[]) arguments amount requirement by writing message in System.err

    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Produce implementing class or interface specified by provided token. Generated class classes name is same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code is placed in the relevant subdirectory of the specified root directory.
      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if:
      • token or root is null;
      • token specify non-class or non-interface objec;
      • token specify private or final class/private interface;
      • This exception was thrown by printClass(Path)

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Produces jar file with implementing class or interface specified by provided token. Generated class classes name is same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added.
      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if:
      • token or jarFile is null;
      • jarFile is not a .jar extended file
      • jarFile has not a parent directory
      • IOException was thrown while creating/deleting directory to store source code
      • This exception was thrown by implement(Class, Path) or compile(Class, Path)

    • collectAbstractMethods

      private List<Method> collectAbstractMethods(Class<?> token)
      Find only declared Method in token inheritance. If token is a class, search recursively, otherwise get all methods by call Class.getMethods() and filter them.
      Parameters:
      token - type token to filter its Method.
      Returns:
      List of Method that were not defined in parent of token.
